Text: I really like how the teams were randomly sorted compared to studio project 1.
As selecting the projects became weighing the skills of the current members and choosing a project which matched the expertise of the team as a whole.
This approach was akin to how teams will be within the work force, however a slight difference is that we had multiple people having similar roles instead of a range of different roles.
For our project we decided to work on Soils Mapping with Logic Studios which is technically working under Alliance Trucking.
This is a great opportunity as it means that we have two clients to work with and gather feedback from.
Kuku (Logic studios) acting more like a supervisor, and thus be of great support whenever developmental problems arise .
While Eric (Alliance Trucking) would be give notes on UI and UX as he would be the user handling the program we are creating.
As for how we are approaching this project, Kuku has given us optional technology stack to work from PHP, MySQL, Google Map API or OpenStreetView.
Our team has yet to properly discuss how we will be approaching this, but even if we look decide to choose different technologies the ideas remain the same.
So currently i am researching on PHP and looking through documentation (PHP manual).
While i have yet to find any ground breaking knowledge that would assist the developmental process, atleast now i know what role PHP plays in the program.
I will like to further look into how PHP and MySQL interacts throughout next week.
Apart from technologies i have also learnt alot from the workshop held on friday, and would like to implement its teachings throughout our developmental cycle.
